        "Zhu QY ,Qin AK ,Suganthan PN ,Huang GB . Evolutionary extreme learning machine. Pattern Recognit. 2005;38(10):1759-63 . Mr. Gopal Singh Kushwah received B.E. degree in Computer science and engineering from RGPV University Bhopal, India in 2008 and M.Tech. degree in Computer science and engineering from MNNIT Allahabad, India in 2011. He has worked for 3 years as an Assistant professor in IPS College of Technology and Management Gwalior, India. At present, he is pursuing Ph.D. in Computer Engineering from NIT Kurukshetra, India. His research interest covers denial of service attack defense, cloud computing, and machine learning. Dr. Virender Ranga has received his Ph.D. degree in 2016 from Computer Engineering Department of National Institute of Technology, Kurukshetra, Haryana, India followed by M.Tech. and B.Tech. degrees. He has published more than 70 research papers in various SCI/SCIE/SCOPUS Journals and reputed International Conferences in the area of Computer Communications. Presently, he is Assistant Professor in the Computer Engineering Department, National Institute of Technology Kurukshetra since 2008. He has been conferred by Young Faculty Award in 2016 for his excellent contributions in the field of Computer Communications. He has been acted as member of TPC in various International conferences of repute. He is a member of editorial board of various reputed journals like Journal of Applied Computer Science & Artificial Intelligence, International Journal of Advances in Computer Science and Information Technology (IJACSIT), Circulation in Computer Science (CCS), International Journal of Bio Based and Modern Engineering (IJBBME) and International Journal of Wireless Networks and Broadband Technologies. He has been acted as Guest Editor for a special issue published in International Journal of Sensors, Wireless Communications and Control (Bentham Science Publication). He is an active reviewer of many reputed journals of IEEE Transactions, IEEE Communications Surveys & Tutorials, Springer, Elsevier, Talyor & Francis, Wiley and InderScience. His research area includes Cloud Security, Wireless Sensor & Adhoc Networks Security, IoT Security, FANET Security, SDN Security, IoRT Security etc."
