    {
      "id": "urn:article:1-s2-0-s0167404824000749-main",
      "type": "schema:ScholarlyArticle",
      "title": "Crayfish optimization algorithm for improving cyber security in cloud computing",
      "authors": [
        "Sahaya Stalin Jose. G",
        "G. Sugitha",
        "Ayshwarya Lakshmi. S",
        "Preethi Bangalore Chaluvaraj"
      ],
      "year": "2024",
      "doi": "10.1016/j.cose.2024.103773",
      "journal": "Computers & Security",
      "abstract": "The decentralized and distributed architecture of cloud computing promotes adoption and growth in various \nsocietal domains, including education, government, information technology, business, entertainment. Cloud \ncomputing (CC) makes a broad range of information technologies available. Security and privacy are key \nchallenges in storing big data in the cloud. To overcome this challenge, a Self-Attention Conditional Generative \nAdversarial Network Optimised with Crayfish Optimization Algorithm for Improving Cyber Security in Cloud \nComputing (CybS-CC-SACGAN -COA) is proposed in this paper to enhance the safety of CC environment. The \ninput data is amassed from NSL-KDD database. After that, the data is fed to pre-processing segment. The segment \nof pre-processing eliminates Cloud data termination and missing value replacement using Reformed Phase \nConserving Vibrant Range Compression filter. The results of pre-processing serves for feature selection. The \noptimal features are selected by means of Manta Ray Foraging Optimization Algorithm (MRFOA). Cloud data is \ncategorized as normal and abnormal data, like Denial-of-Service (DoS), Probe, Remote to local attack (R2L), User \nto root attack (U2R) by the help of SACGAN. Crayfish Optimization Algorithm (COA) is proposed to optimize the \nSACGAN classifier that classifies anomaly data precisely. The proposed CSCC-SACGAN -COA technique is \nactivated in Python under some metrics. The proposed CSCC-SACGAN -COA approach has attained higher \ndetection accuracy, lower computation time, higher AUC, higher scalability and lower detection error rate \ncompared to the existing methods.",
      "keywords": [
        "Cloud computing",
        "Crayfish optimization algorithm",
        "NSL-KDD benchmark dataset",
        "Reformed phase conserving vibrant range",
        "compression filter",
        "Manta ray foraging optimization algorithm and",
        "self-attention conditional generative adversa rial network"
      ],
      "objective": [
        "This work develops the three forms of foraging behaviors: somersault, cyclone and chainforaging provide an efficient optimization paradigm for feature selection. 3.3.1.",
        "Discussion This paper proposes SACGAN optimised with Crayfish Optimization Algorithm to optimize SACGAN network algorithm."
      ],
      "problem": [
        "COA overcomes the manual random and grid explorations probleMs. To strike a Table 3 Nominated Features using Manta Ray Foraging Optimization Algorithm.",
        "The problem solution is repre sented by each column matrix."
      ],
      "methodology": [
        "Cyber security systems (CSS) in platform of cloud tools and techniques are available to identifying attacks on cloud setup (Qureshi et al., 2021 ; Ogwara et al., 2021 ; Samunnisa et al., 2023 ).",
        "Real-time analysis of the complex data generated is necessary for the develop ment of robust intrusion detection systeMs. Therefore, deep learning techniques are promising for the analysis of large data, consisting of traffic flows in cloud networks for indicators of intrusions, even if they have not been detected before.",
        "The proposed system is assessed using network data from the benchmark NSL-KDD dataset."
      ],
      "contributions": [
        "The primary contributions of this paper are abridged below: ≡CybS-CC-SACGAN -COA is proposed for protecting CC environment. ≡The feature selection and categorization method for IDS is explored."
      ],
